A typical Hong Kong tea stall aside the busy commute route of the residents in the area.

A local restaurant Yummy

Cha Chaan Teng by the side of the road, perfect for a short break snacking on some noodles and local style milk tea.
Despite being next to multi lane roads, at a busy intersection it is recessed enough that it quite relaxing sitting outside.
The food is what you would expect from this kind of place, no surprise or disappointment.  The service is friendly and cheerful.

Average price ($30~40/p for lunch), average food (but freshly served).

Iced (lemon) tea is good, and the service is good.
